The topics include specifics of children's literature, importance of fairy tales at pre-school age, classics of children's literature; 20th century Estonian children's literature; modern Estonian children's literature.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of special features of young children's literature, history and classics of Estonian and world's children's literature; to foster students' skills in analysing literary work and using it in teaching.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students will 1) understand specifics of children's literature; 2) know its theoretical aspects and didactic aims; 3) know the classics of Estonian and world children's literature; 4) apply knowledge in practice.
